sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Executes an RFC from the available list for the create, update, or read operation.

Inputs :

  • Connection Alias - Connection alias for SAP S/4HANA - RFC.
  • RFC - Reference to records (SAP RFC Name and Application Component) in SAP S/4HANA - RFC table.
  • Import and Changing Tab Inputs - Input fields from the Import and Changing tab for the selected RFC, represented in a flat structure.
  • Tables Tab Inputs - Input fields from Tables tab for the selected RFC, represented in a flat structure..

Outputs :

  • Response - Response from SAP S/4HANA - RFC for the execution of selected RFC.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in SAP S/4HANA - RFC, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error as returned from SAP S/4HANA - RFC in the RETURN object. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • No or empty response received from SAP ECC - RFC.
  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.

To use this action, the corresponding SAP S/4HANA - RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP_S4HANA_RFC Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Execute RFC
